You are working on the Layman React Native app.

Project goals:
- Warm, polished UI matching peach/orange/cream visual direction
- Fast and reliable mobile UX with smooth transitions
- Clean authentication and session persistence using Supabase
- Article browsing, saving, and search
- Context-aware AI chat ("Ask Layman") with simple responses

Code style:
- TypeScript-first
- Keep components small and readable
- Avoid hardcoding secrets in source files
- Use environment variables for API keys and endpoints
- Prefer clear naming and straightforward logic

UX expectations:
- Rounded cards and warm palette consistency
- Strong readability over images (use overlays/gradients as needed)
- Responsive behavior on both iOS and Android
- Keyboard-safe input layouts for chat and forms

Data and API expectations:
- Supabase handles auth and saved article persistence
- NewsData API powers article feeds/search
- Gemini API powers question suggestions and article-aware chat
